  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "In the adopted hierarchy of energy scales, they are parametrically subleading with respect to the considered in-medium quarkonium potential.",
    "The imaginary part of the in-medium quarkonium potential is proportional to κ(T) r 2 [31,147].• Reaction rates Using the OQS+pNRQCD formalism, we systematically calculate interactions with the medium at strong coupling: our self-energy contributions induce a thermal shift in the quarkonium energy, a thermal quarkonium width and singlet-octet, octet-octet and octet-singlet transitions that describe recombination and account for gluodissociation [148] parton dissociation [149] and screening effects (in the short-distance limit).",
    "We note that the thermal decay width can be computed as either (1) an expansion in E/(π T) with the state of the art expression extending up to order E/(π T) or (2) using the eigenvalue of the non-Hermitian Lagrangian which emerges at a given order in the E/(π T) expansion.",
    "For a detailed discussion of method (1) and explicit expressions, see Sect. 4.1 of Ref.",
    "For this report we use method (2) since, in practice, it provides a better description of the dynamical evolution than using widths based on the vacuum states."
  ],
